---
title: Cuban-Spiced Turkey & Black Bean Tacos with Pineapple Salsa & Crema
description: These quick and hearty tacos are bursting with tropical flavor. Warm flour tortillas are filled with spiced chicken and black beans, then topped with a zesty pineapple-tomato salsa, a dollop of crema, and fresh scallion greens. A final squeeze of lime brings brightness to every bold, savory bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6864bb1d0203e9f8dbb4c788-d238720f.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6864bb1d0203e9f8dbb4c788-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Caribbean
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cuban-spiced-turkey-and-black-bean-tacos-6864bb1d0203e9f8dbb4c788
nutrition:
  calories: 920 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1790 mg
time required: 20 minutes
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce} and roughly chop. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine scallion whites, tomato, pineapple, lime zest, juice from half the lime, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Set aside until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Stir in @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, and half the @Cuban spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat. (The beans will thicken more as they cool.)

Using a #potato masher{} or #fork{}, mash beans until mostly smooth. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Cover and set aside until ready to serve.

While beans cook, open package of @ground turkey{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with remaining Cuban Spice Blend and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates. Fill with chicken and black beans (if beans have too much liquid, use a #slotted spoon{}). Top with pineapple salsa (draining first), crema, and scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.